Just as the dust has started settling on fatality occurrences in South Africa's mining sector, Anglo American Platinum has reported a loss of life of an employee. This comes following a fall of ground related incident which occurred on Thursday, 18 October 2018 at the company’s Dishaba mine in Amandelbult. Anglo American Platinum’s CEO, Chris Griffith, says: “We are all deeply saddened by this tragic incident, and send our sincerest condolences to the family, friends and colleagues of our employee who has lost their life. We are providing support and assistance to all involved during this difficult time." "We remain committed to our objective of eliminating fatalities with a zero-harm mindset and have begun an independent and comprehensive process to understand the circumstances of this incident and to ensure we learn from it to prevent recurrence.”